
fresh corn - refrigerate and use within 2-3 days 

================================================================================
TYPES OF CORN 
================================================================================


yellow corn 
    common uses:    fresh on the cob, soups, salads, cornbread, polenta 
    flavor:         sweet, classic corn taste 
    forms:          fresh, cornmeal, grits 
    chef tip:       ideal for grilling nad caramelizatoin due to natural sugars 

white corn
    common uses:    tortillas, tamales, pozole, hominy 
    flavor:         slightly milder and sweeter than yellow corn 
    forms:          masa harina, fresh kernels 
    chef tip:       preferred in mexican cuisine for authentic masa 

blue corn 
    common uses:    tortillas, chips, pancakesk 
    flavor:         earthy, nutty 
    forms:          blue cornmeal, masa 
    chef tip:       high in anthocyanins (antioxidants); adds color and depth to dishes 

red corn
    common uses:    decorative dishes, specialty tortillas, salads 
    flavor:         rich, slightly nutty 
    chef tip:       often used in hierloom recipes, adds visual appeal

sweet corn (fresh) 
    common uses:    pozole, grits, masa for tortillas 
    flavor:         mild, slightly alkaline 
    chef tip:       essential for authentic latin american dishes 

popcorn 
    common uses:    snacks, caramel corn, savory seasonings 
    flavor:         neutral, takes on seasoning well 
    chef tip:       use clarified butter or flavored oils for gourmet versions 

heirloom varieties
    examples:       glass gem (multicolor), cherokee white eagle, hopi blue 
    uses:           specialty dishes, artisan tortillas 

================================================================================
COMMON PROCESSED FORMS 
================================================================================

Type            Description                 Uses
cornmeal        ground dried corn           used for cornbread, polenta 
masa harina     lime-treated cornmeal       tortillas, tamales 
corn flour      fine grind                  baking 
corn starch                                 thicken agent for sauces & desserts
hominy & grits  alkali-treated kernels      southern dishes 


================================================================================
COOKING METHODS
================================================================================

Boiling / Steaming - for fresh corn on the cob 
Grilling / Roasting - enhances sweetness & smoky flavor 
Dry Milling - for cornmeal & corn flour 
Nixtamalization - treating corn with lime for masa


================================================================================
FLAVOR PAIRINGS 
================================================================================

sweet - butter, cream, herbs, cheese 
savory - chili, lime, smoked meats 


================================================================================
CHEF TIPS  
================================================================================

cook quickly after harvest, sugars convert to starch rapidly 
balance the sweetness and acidity - lime & vinegar are good additions 
nixtamalization for authentic tortillas / tamales is an interesting option 
experiment with corn in desserts - corn pudding, ice cream 
